sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M31415
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A refactored part of the M13KO7 genome. Separates overlapping parts if possible, and inserts zero cutters in between parts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephanie Nix
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Homologous recombination, redesigning existing genes to get rid of existing overlap.
